      <section class="hero" style="--hero-image: url('images/baking-mother-home-child-kitchen.webp')"><div class="hero-inner"><div class="hero-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Our home</p><h1>A home designed around the children who live in it</h1><p>Our residential home has been arranged to feel calm, safe and genuinely welcoming, with spaces for privacy, routine, connection and emotional regulation.</p><div class="hero-actions"><a class="button" href="referrals">Enquire About a Placement</a><a class="button secondary" href="contact">Request a Visit</a></div></div></div></section>
      <section class="section story-grid">
        <div class="story-copy"><p class="section-label">Inside the home</p><h2>Small, personal and thoughtfully arranged</h2><p>Our home accommodates up to three young people at a time, ensuring every child receives individualised attention without the overwhelm of a larger group setting.</p><ul class="check-list"><li>Three private en-suite bedrooms with space for personal expression.</li><li>Two reception rooms for relaxing, socialising and unwinding.</li><li>Dedicated dining room and fully equipped kitchen for routines and life skills.</li><li>Sensory room for emotional regulation and therapeutic support.</li><li>Secure private rear garden for outdoor play, reflection and fresh air.</li><li>Staff office kept separate from the living space.</li></ul></div>
        <figure class="image-panel"><img src="images/happy-family-spending-time-together-home.webp" alt="Warm home environment with family-style time together" loading="lazy" /><figcaption class="image-caption">A calm setting for everyday life</figcaption></figure>
      </section>
      <section class="band blue"><div class="section"><p class="section-label">Community</p><h2>Connected to schools, health services and local life</h2><p class="section-intro">The home is located with access to transport, schools, GP services, dental care, opticians, parks, leisure facilities, libraries, places of worship and youth organisations.</p><div class="grid three"><article class="feature"><h3>Education</h3><p>Access to local schools, study routines and educational support.</p></article><article class="feature"><h3>Health</h3><p>Registration with GP, dental and optician services on admission.</p></article><article class="feature"><h3>Belonging</h3><p>Children are supported to build community, friendships and positive routines.</p></article></div></div></section>
      <section class="section story-grid reverse">
        <div class="story-copy"><p class="section-label">Identity</p><h2>Supporting every identity</h2><p>We actively support each young person's cultural, religious and personal identity as part of everyday life at Animate Care.</p><ul class="check-list"><li>Access to places of worship and local religious communities.</li><li>Dietary requirements linked to culture, religion or health.</li><li>Birthdays, festivals and religious occasions led by the child's wishes.</li><li>Culturally appropriate clothing, healthcare and lifestyle support.</li></ul></div>
        <figure class="image-panel small"><img src="images/side-view-children-planting-seeds-home.webp" alt="Children planting seeds together at home" loading="lazy" /><figcaption class="image-caption">Growing confidence and belonging</figcaption></figure>
      </section>
      <section class="band"><div class="section"><p class="section-label">Safety</p><h2>Safety built into every corner</h2><div class="grid four"><article class="feature"><h3>Risk Assessment</h3><p>Clear plans for each child and the shared home environment.</p></article><article class="feature"><h3>Fire Safety</h3><p>Procedures, checks and routines that protect children and staff.</p></article><article class="feature"><h3>Internet Safety</h3><p>Digital boundaries and support for safe online behaviour.</p></article><article class="feature"><h3>DBS Staff</h3><p>Safer recruitment and fully checked staff before working with children.</p></article></div></div></section>
      <section class="section"><h2>Our home: questions answered</h2><div class="faq-list"><details class="faq-item"><summary>How many children can live at Animate Care?</summary><p>Animate Care accommodates up to three young people at a time.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Does Animate Care have private bedrooms?</summary><p>Yes. Each child has a private en-suite bedroom designed for comfort, privacy and personal expression.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Does Animate Care have a sensory room?</summary><p>Yes. The sensory room supports emotional regulation and therapeutic care.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Is the home connected to the community?</summary><p>Yes. Children can access education, healthcare, transport, parks, cultural venues and community activities.</p></details></div></section>
